By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Saturday confirmed that 162 new cases of #COVID-19 were recorded in Nigeria. According to the report released via it’s twitter handle, the 162 new cases were recorded from 16 out of 36 states of the federation and the FCT as follows: Lagos-53; Gombe-21; Oyo-19; Delta-12;Ondo-11; Plateau-10; Ebonyi-9; FCT-6;Kwara-6; Kaduna-5; Rivers-3; Ogun and Anambra-2 each; Imo-2 and Ekiti-1. The health agency noted that the total confirmed cases is now 54,905 our of which42,922 have been discharged while 1,054 lives have been lost to the novel virus pandemic since index case was recorded in late February, 2020 in the country. See table below for the state by state total recorded cases ; By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The latest COVID-19 report released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has it that a total of 46,577 cases have been confirmed in Nigeria as 437 new infections were recorded on Sunday. The NCDC while disclosed this via its official twitter handle… August 10, 2020 In "News" By Abujah Racheal ABUJA - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has recorded 404  new COVID-19 cases in the country, as total infections from the virus rise to 42,208. The NCDC made this known on its official twitter handle on Wednesday. The health agency noted that five more persons… July 30, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The latest update from the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has revealed that 601 new cases of COVID-19 were recorded in Nigeria on Saturday. This brings the the total confirmed cases to 51,905 out of which 38,767 have been discharged after their… August 23, 2020 In "Top Stories"